### We spoke to young adults with Type 1 diabetes to talk about sex, dating
Sex, dating and relationships can be awkward for everyone, and worrying how
Type 1 diabetes might get in the way is normal. We talked to three different
couples about those awkward moments when it feels like Type 1 diabetes just
Hypos in the heat of the moment. Insulin pump tangles. Plans screwed up to
They also talked about how they deal with Type 1 diabetes in their
relationship day-to-day, and about what it means to have someone supporting
you through the ups and downs of diabetes.
When Type 1 tries its hardest to ruin a good night, sometimes all you need is
your testing kit, some perseverance and a supportive partner...
When Ted found himself out for dinner with Storm, he had more than just first
It's natural to worry about telling your new partner about your diabetes. It's
difficult to open up to people sometimes but there isn't a right or wrong time
Give them a small explanation of what diabetes is, about how you treat it and
what things like hypos are. You don't have to go into loads of detail straight
away, your diabetes is just another part of you that your partner will get to
When Fawn and Chesney first started dating as teenagers, Fawn tried to hide
her Type 1 diabetes. It took an awkward car journey with her mum for Chesney
